The paper deals with content filtering for video social networks, which involves analyzing video content to detect unwanted content related to high-level semantic concepts such as pornography and violence. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to multimedia analysis and processing, such as cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper proposes a method that combines diverse evidence from different features and video elements, which could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
